<br>
I didn't have to be there until 8 in the morning this year (yesterday), but it was crazy.  The parking lot was packed to the max, people were just going crazy.  We were also understaffed for the day, the reasoning I heard was that we weren't as busy last year so they didn't think we needed more people. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :ebr --><img src=http://www.geocities.com/anne_g_ivy/eyebrow.gif ALT=":ebr"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm like - if I didn't have to work, I'd have still been in bed asleep.  I would NEVER go shopping the day after Thanksgiving.  NEVER!  I don't mind paying a little more to avoid the hostile crowds of people.  But that's just me - I don't like big crowds, especially big crowds of shoppers.  I'm more likely to do my shopping on a weekday during the day when kids are at school and most adults are generally at work.  I prefer it being quieter and less hassled.<br>
<br>
I agree esdras, the spokeswoman was being insensitive.  Bad public relations.  Good public relations would have given her the dvd player for free and maybe even a 10% off coupon for a future visit.  Shoot, the player was only $29.99, surely the store has enough funds to cover that.  Stores do set aside funds for different things, they could do that.  But we're talking Wal-Mart, a cheapy store.  Perfect for cheap customers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Does anyone else think the Wal-Mart commercials are some of the most annoying commercials out there?  Honestly, because of their commercials, I hardly ever go to Wal-Mart anymore.  To me, their commercials makes me think that their stores are of very poor quality and I don't want to shop cheapskate to where I know the merchandise isn't as good.  And their merchandise isn't very good quality for the most part. <p>**********************************************<br>
